HEADWORD: Conjurator
<hw>Con"ju*ra`tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.]</ety>
<fld>(O. Eng. Law)</fld> <def>One who swears or is sworn with others;
one bound by oath with others; a compurgator.</def>
<rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
